               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-962" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-962" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-962" type="surname" value="BUHRER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-962" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM BUHRER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a glass dealer, living in Skinner-street, Snow-hill. On the 4th of February, at half-past nine o'clock, I was in Holborn, and felt a tug at my pocket—I turned, and saw this man run away—I felt my pocket was empty—he ran faster, when I called "Stop thief"—he ran as far as Gray's-inn-lane, and the constable stopped him—this is my handkerchief—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>)—he is the man I saw near me, and the one that ran away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I picked it up. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. He was the only man that was running—I followed him till near the time he was taken—I had felt it safe not a minute before, and I had not dropped it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-963" type="witnessName">
